    • Constructor Detail

      • CPSConnection

        public CPSConnection(java.lang.String cns,
                     java.lang.String storage,
                     java.lang.String username,
                     java.lang.String password)
              throws java.lang.Exception
        Constructs an instance of the Connection class. Note that it doesn't necessarily make a connection to CPS when the constructor is called. To specify document root tag and document id path please use other constructor CPSConnection(String, String, String, String, String, String). Default tag name for document root is "document" and document ID path "//document/id".
        Parameters:
        cns - Specifies the connection string, such as tcp://127.0.0.1:5550
        storage - The name of the storage you want to connect to
        username - Username for authenticating with the storage
        password - Password for this user
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
